This paper deals with discovering visual attributes in images using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel training procedure for CNNs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a dataset, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.IR.
